claims:
1. A universal bacterial assay for detecting and monitoring changes in concentration of a target analyte in solution, said assay comprising:
creating a reaction solution comprising a high affinity protein-based sensor and a test bacteria dispersed in an aqueous solution, wherein the sensor comprises a bacterial high affinity binding protein engineered with a detectable label that generates a detectable signal;
adding a target analyte to said reaction solution, wherein high affinity binding protein is specific for said target analyte, and wherein said target analyte is a metal or metallated complex;
exposing said reaction solution to an energy source to generate said detectable signal; and
detecting changes in the detectable signal in the reaction solution over time, wherein said changes correspond to interaction of said test strain with said target analyte.

29. A kit for conducting universal bacterial assay for detecting and monitoring changes in concentration of a target analyte in solution, said kit comprising:
a high affinity protein-based sensor comprising a high affinity binding protein engineered with a detectable label that generates a detectable signal, wherein high affinity binding protein is a bacterial protein specific for a metallated target analyte;
optionally, an amount of said target analyte;
instructions for creating a reaction solution with said high affinity protein-based sensor, a test bacteria strain, and said target analyte;
instructions for exposing said reaction solution to an energy source to generate said detectable signal; and
instructions for detecting changes in the detectable signal in the reaction solution over time to determine the interaction of said test bacterial strain with said target analyte.
